I"<p>Note: My thoughts on this have changed, more in line with Footnote (4).<sup id="fnref:aside" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:aside" class="footnote" rel="footnote">1</a></sup>  Winning, as I understand it now, requires treating yourself neither as an underdog nor as an overdog, but a <a href="https://x.com/bawhatever/status/1844771819930210515">true appraisal</a>  of your feelings, your abilities, your environment, and your opponent moment by moment. This requires self-awareness, vulnerability, honesty, and self respect. With this comes acceptance, relaxation, and energy that sets you free.</p>

